{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"stem-poker-gecko","description":"`rebar review-plan` (the four-pass plan-review gate) is **non-deterministic and mis-calibrated**\nas a gate: the same ticket re-reviewed gives different PASS/BLOCK verdicts and a different finding\nset each run, the advisory batch is a near-constant ~10 regardless of plan quality, and almost\nevery finding is tagged `severity=critical` while remaining non-blocking. The Pass-1 finder\nrecall is stochastic, so \"PASS\" is not reproducible for the same input — which undermines a gate\nwhose contract is \"must PASS before you can claim.\" (The finding CONTENT is consistently high\nquality; this bug is about stability/calibration, not correctness.)\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n1. Run `rebar review-plan <id> --output json` on a well-formed ticket; note `verdict` + the\n   `blocking`/`advisory` arrays.\n2. Without changing the ticket (or after a change that only ADDS detail/hardening), re-run.\n3. Compare verdicts, finding counts, and which findings appear.\n\n## Expected\n- The verdict is reproducible for the same input (same ticket -> same PASS/BLOCK), and finding\n  count/severity reflect actual plan quality (a strong plan yields fewer/lower-severity findings\n  than a weak one).\n\n## Actual (observed across ~29 runs this session on epic d251 + its children)\n- **Non-reproducible verdicts.** S4/S6/S7 went `PASS -> BLOCK` after remediations that only added\n  hardening, and each re-run surfaced DIFFERENT blocking findings; S6's block count was\n  non-monotonic across rounds: `0 -> 3 -> 1 -> 6`. The same plan can pass for one run and block\n  for the next.\n- **Fixed-size advisory batch.** Almost every ticket, every round, returned ~10 advisories\n  (`P/10a` near-uniformly; one ticket once at 8) — reads as a target/cap, not a measurement, so\n  advisory volume does not discriminate plan quality.\n- **Severity inflation.** Most advisories are `severity=critical` (e.g. epic 10/10, S3 10/10)\n  yet non-blocking (`reason: default-advisory`) — \"critical but doesn't block\" is incoherent and\n  makes severity useless for triage.\n- **Weak cross-criterion dedup.** A single root issue surfaced as multiple findings under\n  different criteria (e.g. S1's `use_lockfile`/TF>=1.10 issue appeared 4x under T1/T3/E2/G6),\n  inflating the count.\n\n## Impact\n\"Re-run until it passes\" (the gate protocol) assumes convergence that doesn't hold: remediating\nthe cited block can surface new, unrelated blocks, so a good-faith author may not reach a stable\nPASS. Two agents reviewing the same ticket can get different claimability.\n\n## Notes\n- Likely root: Pass-3 (decide) is deterministic GIVEN the findings, but Pass-1 (finder) recall is\n  stochastic, so determinism is only conditional on a non-deterministic input. The fixed-~10 and\n  all-critical patterns suggest finder prompt/threshold calibration. Surfaced dogfooding d251.\n- Separate, more clear-cut bug filed for signed-on-BLOCK.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Re-running `review-plan` on an unchanged ticket yields a stable verdict (PASS stays PASS;\n      no spurious PASS<->BLOCK flips) — e.g. via seeding/caching the finder, lowered temperature,\n      or a deterministic finder pass, measured over N repeat runs.\n- [ ] Advisory count reflects actual issues found (not a near-constant ~10); document/justify any\n      cap and surface when findings were truncated.\n- [ ] Severity is calibrated so `critical` implies blocking (or the block thresholds are aligned\n      so a wall of \"critical\" advisories cannot coexist with a clean PASS); severity becomes\n      usable for triage.\n- [ ] Cross-criterion dedup collapses one root issue reported under multiple criteria into a\n      single finding.\n- [ ] docs/plan-review-gate.md documents the determinism guarantees and the calibration of\n      severity vs. blocking thresholds.","id":"3bdf-2b18-f73d-45b0","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":["plan-review","llm","gate"],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"plan-review: non-deterministic verdict + mis-calibrated findings (fixed ~10 advisories, all 'critical', PASS<->BLOCK flips)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782699759391055001,"uuid":"53be04c1-8bd3-4284-931d-1b715702cdb2"}